Package: xhelix
Version: 0.0.11-4
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: xhelix authors <maintainers@xhelix.dev>
Depends: libc6
Recommends: nftables, auditd
Suggests: apparmor
Description: Real-time Linux runtime security agent
 xhelix observes processes, files, network, identity, and memory
 events in real time and produces high-signal security alerts. It
 ships with an active response engine, TLS-protected enterprise UI,
 integrated security audit (xhelix doctor), elite-tier detection
 (beacon, tamperguard, kintegrity, threat feeds, DNS exfil), and a
 per-binary behavioural baseline aggregator with set-diff + EWMA
 anomaly scoring. Optional fleet-hub upload (see xhub) for
 cross-host baselines.
 .
 Single static binary, no external dependencies, runs under systemd
 with strict capability hardening.
Homepage: https://github.com/xhelix/xhelix
